                            &lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve used the gilded rose kata with various groups, and I think it is a good one. Before you can start refactoring, you have to write a bunch of tests, and you can practice designing really good ones. If you do it properly, you won&#039;t have time in 45 minutes to get to the refactoring part.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have another refactoring kata that I think I&#039;m going to suggest as an alternative for the participants in my code retreat. (About 1/3 of the people there will have already been to at least one of my previous code retreats, so I think they in particular might appreciate doing something different.)&lt;/p&gt;
